Hey, Next Level! I appreciate you sending me your music. I liked the drum set playing here. The guitar tone is vibrant.

Sadly, the vocal arrangement felt a bit monotonous and could use more dynamic phrasing. Thus, I am unable to proceed at this time. Please pardon the bluntness of my comments; they are just my personal observations and not meant to discourage you.

Your talent is clear, so please continue creating music. Warm regards and good luck

Lovely arrangement you have here in "Christmas at Rockefeller Center", Next Level. I also appreciate the vocal runs and the control. However, the feel of the track doesn't quite fit my current picks. I hope you find the perfect playlist for this well made track. Thank you for sharing your art with me.

Vielen herzlichen herzlichen Dank für diese Einsendung. Das ist definitiv entsorgen mit viel Potenzial. Im Grunde mag ich den Retro vibe sehr. Weihnachtssong jeglicher Art haben bei mir leider keinen Platz. Tut mir leid, dass ich hier so strikt sein muss. Denn obwohl ich das Weihnachtsfest feiere, will ich diese einfach nicht auf meiner Playlist haben.

Heya, and thank you for sending Next Level's Christmas at Rockefeller Center my way this time around! I quite appreciated the nice voice and the chill groove, the song felt pleasant and flowed smoothly, but, forgive me, my "different" Christmas playlist is focused on alternative / indie / or folky Christmas tracks, and retro soul simply felt, stylistically, too far from that, I am sorry. I invite you to check the playlist for a sound reference, and hope the song gets the attention it deserves even if not a style match for me here. Love, T.

Feedback:
Hey! 

Thanks for reaching out to Vibey Curator and sharing your art! 

I think that the track works perfectly within its genre, I like the personality of the vocals and the arrangement and instrumentation are solid as well. My only issue is that this is away from the vibe of my "Nu-Funk | Alt R&B | Indie Soul" playlist as I'm looking for something groovier and preferably with a more modern kind of production, I think that you'll see that too if you give it a listen or check out the artists featured.

Despite that, I see talent here, I'm sure you will find your spot with other curators closer to your style. 

Greetings from Barcelona! 

Jordi - Vibey Curator

Hey Next Level, 

While you do have that soulful christmas sound, generally I'm looking for a much moodier sound for a soul sub. Meaning a slightly slower groove, and slightly more "suffering" sound, if that makes. Something that says my heart is crying. Your sound is lovely, but also very bright and "positive".

Keeping to a "sadder" sort of blues in the future would be what I'd be looking for, to make your song a great fit!

VH
